posts.author: lindalouwho
posts.text:
Ivo Shandor : The Jerusalem Embassy Act of 1995 is a public law of the United States passed by the 104th Congress on October 23, 1995. It was passed for the purposes of initiating and funding the relocation of the Embassy of the United States in Israel from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem, no later than May 31, 1999 [...]
Even from the Embassy Act's legislative beginnings, the question of Congress' over-reach and if somehow it was usurping the Executive's authority or power over matters of foreign affairs had played subtle role in shaping the debate at the time. President Clinton had taken the unusual step of not signing the Embassy Act into law once Congress had presented it to him but rather let 10 days of inaction pass, allowing the bill to return to Congress and automatically become law by Constitutional "default" to show his disapproval.
Yep, they had way more than enough votes to override a Presidential veto.

posts.author: TheITGuy
posts.title: Greetings from Italy
posts.text:
Greetings from Italy Hi everybody!
I'm new here so let me introduce myself...
I'm a home-grower since 2013 and a cannabis passionate and recreational user since... forever
I started my growing experience with a completely homemade growbox and very little knowledge of cannabis cultivation, but a lot of good will and strong motivation in growing my own pot even if the whole thing was and is against the law (a stupid law imho).
I made a lot of mistakes but in less than 3 month I got my first harvest. It was a very little harvest and possibly a poor quality one, but no joy was ever bigger than smoking my own cannabis
Since than growing cannabis is my main drive.
In time my knowledge has grown and my growbox has improved too.
Now I'm 32 years old, I live alone and grow pot in my basement. I have a little room (barely 3m x 1,5m) fully organized to contain two growboxes 1 square meter each.
That is my play park, my secret place, my PotCave (this is how I named it ).
I also have a degree in IT and i'm just now engaging in a project to automate a lot of processes in the PotCave with an Arduino powered system.
The PotCave is under continuous upgrade with new ideas for improvements coming to my mind every day and possibly soon I'll open a dedicated thread with a complete description hoping that with your help it will became more advanced and professional.
Since growing is such a passion for me, I would like to do it professionally, but unfortunately for me in my country is still illegal growing or selling marijuana even for medical purposes. So I'm looking outside my country for a legal job in the cannabis industry.
My two options right now are Spain and Canada (I'd love US too but I think is probably harder to get a Visa there), but really I don't have a clear idea of how to get a job in the cannabis industry for a foreigner like me.
Do you have any suggestions or can you link me any discussions about that?
I think it's all for now folks.
I'm really excited to be part of the 420 family and hope to meet many new 420 friends and maybe even get my dream job.
Bye for now
Love you and Stay High! improvise liked this post

posts.title: Ireland's government expects UK to make new Brexit proposal
posts.text:
Ireland's government expects UK to make new Brexit proposal Posted: Updated: (AP Photo/Kirsty Wigglesworth). Britain's Prime Minister Theresa May leaves 10 Downing Street to attend the weekly session of Prime Ministers Questions in Parliament in London, Wednesday, Dec. 6, 2017. 
LONDON (AP) - Ireland's government expects Britain to make a new proposal on Brexit by Friday as officials in London struggle to resolve issues surrounding the Irish border that are stalling talks with the European Union. 
British Prime Minister Theresa May is under pressure to persuade EU leaders who meet next week to declare that sufficient progress has been made on divorce issues, such as the Irish border, so that trade talks can begin. Business leaders warn further delays will cause trouble for companies as they plan for the future. 
Ireland's prime minister, Leo Varadkar, said Wednesday he hopes May will submit a new formal written offer "tonight or tomorrow." 
Disagreements about how to treat the border between the Republic of Ireland and the U.K. province of Northern Ireland derailed an earlier proposal.

thread.title: Iberostar Grand Hotel
thread.title_full: Iberostar Grand Hotel Budapest (Budapest, Hongrie) | Expedia.fr

posts.author: expedia.com
posts.text: It’s walking distance from the Parliament, US Embassy and St Stephens Basilica. We had an amazing time at the Christmas Market which was within a five minute walk from the hotel. Its an upscale hotel for a very reasonable price, unbeatable five star service and just an upstanding group of folks working for the hotel that made our stay so memorable. Every time we get back at our room we find a little gift that represents the warmness of their city and took the time entertain our son with a few activities to keep him busy. The spa and amenities of the hotel is upscale and the restaurant in the hotel had one of the most amazing acoustic bands that made it feel like being in a concert. We are definitely coming back to Budapest and we are definitely staying with Iberostar again, it’s a home away from home!
